From ea65ecc947e2ae267fe2bccbaaba70a030ab2abe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter Bergin <peter@berginkonsult.se>
Date: Fri, 20 Feb 2026 08:33:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Prepend Modules_CUDA_fix to CMAKE_MODULE_PATH

OE's cmake toolchain file prepends the sysroot cmake modules directory
(${STAGING_DATADIR}/cmake/Modules/) to CMAKE_MODULE_PATH before the
project starts. PyTorch's cmake/public/cuda.cmake only APPENDs its own
Modules_CUDA_fix directory, so the sysroot's FindCUDA.cmake (and its
bundled select_compute_arch.cmake) is found first.

The sysroot cmake may be too old to recognise newer CUDA compute
architectures. For example, on Tegra264 (sm_110, compute capability
11.0), the old select_compute_arch.cmake regex ^([0-9]\.[0-9])$ only
matches single-digit major versions and rejects "11.0", whereas
PyTorch's own upstream/FindCUDA/select_compute_arch.cmake uses
^([0-9]+\.[0-9][af]?)$ which correctly matches "11.0".

Use list(PREPEND ...) so that Modules_CUDA_fix is searched before any
sysroot cmake modules, ensuring PyTorch's up-to-date FindCUDA (which
includes upstream/FindCUDA/select_compute_arch.cmake via an absolute
path) is always used.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE Specific]

AI-Generated: Uses Claude

Signed-off-by: Peter Bergin <peter@berginkonsult.se>
Signed-off-by: Peter Bergin <peter.bergin@1x.tech>
---
 cmake/public/cuda.cmake | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/cmake/public/cuda.cmake b/cmake/public/cuda.cmake
index bc8855d23..7c3146020 100644
--- a/cmake/public/cuda.cmake
+++ b/cmake/public/cuda.cmake
@@ -7,7 +7,7 @@ endif()

 # sccache is only supported in CMake master and not in the newest official
 # release (3.11.3) yet. Hence we need our own Modules_CUDA_fix to enable sccache.
-list(APPEND CMAKE_MODULE_PATH ${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/../Modules_CUDA_fix)
+list(PREPEND CMAKE_MODULE_PATH ${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/../Modules_CUDA_fix)

 # We don't want to statically link cudart, because we rely on it's dynamic linkage in
 # python (follow along torch/cuda/__init__.py and usage of cudaGetErrorName).
